Vintage style illustration of an old-fashioned lion tamer in a circus ring, wearing a red coat and holding a wooden chair, facing a large mechanical beast made of interconnected table grids and spreadsheet cells instead of a lion. The creature's body is composed of rows and columns that shift and jump erratically, some cells expanding while others collapse. Dramatic spotlight illuminates the scene from above, casting long shadows on the sawdust-covered circus floor. Warm sepia tones with pops of crimson and gold, aged paper texture overlay, ornate decorative border framing the scene in the style of vintage circus posters from the 1920s.
